                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/182</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Leavell</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-21T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 21, 1917—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You may seek appropriate opportunity to intimate to President Estrada Cabrera
                    that Government of United States is in receipt of reports indicating that
                    ammunition has recently been shipped from Guatemala to those persons who are now
                    assuming to exercise governmental functions in Costa Rica and who have not been
                    recognized by the Government of the United States.</p>
                <p>You will say that this Government would appreciate authoritative information in
                    regard to these reports.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
